verbs.description: arborise (third-person singular simple present arborises, present participle arborising, simple past and past participle arborised)

examples: The nerve fibre arborises into multiple branches.

entries.meaning: (transitive) To cause (something) to develop a tree-like appearance.
examples: Tall, wide shrubs take up a huge amount of space in a small garden, so remove the lower limbs to provide more space underneath.  […]  When you “arborize” the shrub by limbing it up, you’ll discover an elegant, multi-trunked structure  […]

entries.meaning: (transitive) To penetrate or fill (an area) with a tree-like structure.
examples: The imitation neurones I am composed of agitate their dendrites like mad ganglia that arborize the system as the cell bodies dance along the axis cylinder within the fibres of the foot that isn’t there  […]
